      "comment": "JAKE PERALTA (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fifth (23.21) in a Mix 3/4 at Maitland. Has a good record at this journey. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Has winning claims on his best figures. BALLOW'S REVENGE (3) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 5 lengths from the winner (17.95). Should be in this for a long way. RAIDER DONKEY (2) did a good job to finish second last time out over 324m at this track (17.95) in a Grade 5, the second top-three finish on the trot. Well placed here and can atone this time. TILLY THE FILLY (8) looks an each-way chance.",
